01:37.619 --> 01:41.013
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.144 --> 01:43.581
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.712 --> 01:46.454
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.817 --> 02:03.253
-[LIGHT ROCK MUSIC]

03:09.101 --> 03:10.320
-HEY WATCH OUT!

03:15.151 --> 03:16.457
[GASPING]

03:20.156 --> 03:21.070
HELP!

03:37.652 --> 03:40.394
-MATT: WELL HOW DO YOU LIKE
THAT, SAVED BY THE BLIMP.

03:41.960 --> 03:44.006
-[ROCK MUSIC]

04:00.109 --> 04:00.936
-HEY.

04:01.066 --> 04:01.893
-HEY, WAIT A SECOND.

04:03.112 --> 04:04.809
I'M ON SWITCHBOARD AGAIN?

04:04.940 --> 04:06.724
THAT'S TWICE THIS
WEEK, STEPHANIE.

04:06.855 --> 04:07.943
-I KNOW.

04:08.073 --> 04:09.553
-WELL DO YOU WANNA TELL ME WHY?

04:10.206 --> 04:11.163
-I NEED YOU THERE.

04:11.686 --> 04:13.775
-THAT IS COMPLETELY
UNFAIR, STEPHANIE.

04:13.905 --> 04:15.907
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO
GET STUCK ON SWITCHBOARD
MORE THAN ONCE A WEEK.

04:17.082 --> 04:18.779
YOU KNOW, STEPHANIE,
I REALLY FEEL LIKE

04:18.910 --> 04:20.695
YOU'RE TAKING ADVANTAGE OF
ME BECAUSE I'M YOUR SISTER.

04:21.565 --> 04:23.306
YOU WOULDN'T DO THIS
TO MATT OR C.J.,

04:23.437 --> 04:24.873
WHY AM I GETTING THE
SHORT END OF THE STICK?

04:25.743 --> 04:28.093
-LOOK, I KNOW YOU GOT A LOT
OF EXPERIENCE WHILE I WAS AWAY,

04:28.224 --> 04:29.834
BUT I'VE BEEN NOTICING
YOU'RE STILL PRONE

04:29.965 --> 04:31.271
TO MAKING ROOKIE MISTAKES.

04:31.401 --> 04:32.489
-ROOKIE MISTAKES?

04:33.882 --> 04:35.057
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN, STEPHANIE,

04:35.187 --> 04:36.363
DO YOU WANT TO
GIVE ME AN EXAMPLE?

04:36.493 --> 04:38.060
-DON'T TAKE IT SO PERSONALLY.

04:39.104 --> 04:40.932
YOU'VE COME A LONG WAY IN
A SHORT PERIOD OF TIME.

04:41.063 --> 04:42.151
I'M REALLY PROUD OF YOU.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.544
-BUT YOU DON'T TRUST ME.

04:44.893 --> 04:46.503
-I THINK YOU NEED
A LITTLE SEASONING.

04:46.634 --> 04:48.984
-AND I'M SUPPOSED TO GET
THAT ON SWITCHBOARD DUTY?

04:52.335 --> 04:53.728
-I'LL PUT YOU ON A
TOWER TOMORROW, OKAY?

04:56.644 --> 04:57.688
NOW LET'S GET TO WORK.

05:13.095 --> 05:14.836
HEY, CAN I GIVE YOU A HAND?

05:14.966 --> 05:17.534
-GOT IT, OKAY ON THREE,
ONE, TWO, THREE.

05:18.448 --> 05:20.232
ANY WORD ON THE OTHER SCARAB?

05:20.363 --> 05:21.843
-YEAH, SHOULD BE OUT OF THE
SHOP BY THE END OF THIS WEEK.

05:22.713 --> 05:23.975
-I'M GONNA NEED IT
SOONER THAN THAT.

05:24.106 --> 05:25.934
-WHY? WE SEEM
OKAY WITH ONE BOAT.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.371
-EVER HEARD OF RICHARD BRANSON?

05:28.502 --> 05:30.547
-RICHARD BRANSON,
I DON'T THINK SO.
IS HE A LIFEGUARD?

05:30.678 --> 05:32.636
-NO, NO, NO, HE'S A BRITISH
BUSINESSMAN, YOU KNOW,

05:32.767 --> 05:34.551
ACROSS THE ATLANTIC
IN A HOT AIR BALLOON.

05:34.682 --> 05:36.031
-OH YEAH, I'VE READ ABOUT HIM.

05:36.161 --> 05:37.598
HE'S A BIG DAREDEVIL, HE DOES

05:37.728 --> 05:39.251
ALL THESE CRAZY
STUNTS AND EVERYTHING.

05:39.382 --> 05:40.383
-YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE
WHAT HE'S UP TO NOW.

05:42.037 --> 05:43.560
-SOMETHING TELLS ME
I DON'T WANNA KNOW.

05:43.691 --> 05:46.476
-HE'S GONNA WATER
SKI BEHIND HIS BLIMP.

05:46.607 --> 05:47.869
-NO.

05:48.913 --> 05:49.740
WHERE?

05:49.871 --> 05:50.654
-LONG BEACH HARBOR.

05:50.785 --> 05:52.308
-WHY?

05:52.439 --> 05:54.397
-HE WANTS TO BE IN THE
GUINNESS BOOK OF WORLD RECORDS.

05:54.528 --> 05:55.920
-FOR WHAT, GIVING
LIFEGUARDS GRAY HAIR?

05:56.051 --> 05:58.880
-NOPE, THE LONGEST WATER
SKI BEHIND AN AIR SHIP.

05:59.707 --> 06:01.839
-MITCH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU AGREED TO THIS.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.972
-I DIDN'T, THE CHIEF
ASSIGNED ME TO IT.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.627
HE WANTS US TO STOP BY IN
CASE ANYTHING GOES WRONG.

06:07.715 --> 06:09.107
-WATER SKIING BEHIND A BLIMP.

06:09.238 --> 06:11.240
-NO, WHILE WATER SKIING
BEHIND AN AIR SHIP.

06:12.023 --> 06:13.373
-WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE?

06:13.503 --> 06:15.375
-UH, WELL THE BLIMP
IS BIG AND ROUND--

06:15.505 --> 06:17.812
-[LIVELY MUSIC]

06:29.563 --> 06:30.390
-OH!

06:31.303 --> 06:32.870
-I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.

06:33.001 --> 06:33.871
-OH, IT'S OKAY.

06:34.655 --> 06:36.265
WHAT NOW, DID I BRING
YOU THE WRONG ORDER?

06:36.396 --> 06:37.397
-NO, NO.

06:38.180 --> 06:39.921
-NO? THEN WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

06:40.051 --> 06:43.054
-I JUST WANTED TO TELL YA,
THIS IS A KILLER TUNA MELT.

06:43.185 --> 06:44.665
-REALLY? YOU LIKE IT?

06:44.795 --> 06:45.709
-BEST THING I EVER HAD.

06:45.840 --> 06:47.232
-YES! THAT'S MAURICE.

06:47.363 --> 06:48.799
-WHO'S MAURICE?

06:48.930 --> 06:49.800
-HE'S MY NEW COOK.

06:50.627 --> 06:51.411
-HEY MAURICE!

06:54.109 --> 06:55.066
-YAY!

06:56.198 --> 06:58.592
-COME ON LADS, HAVE A HEART.

07:00.637 --> 07:03.074
SURELY YOU CAN SPARE
A FEW TENS OR 20S.

07:03.205 --> 07:05.337
LET'S GO, COME ON, COUGH IT UP.

07:06.687 --> 07:07.514
-I'LL BE BACK.

07:10.734 --> 07:12.475
-WATCH WHERE YOU'RE GOING, LOVE.

07:12.606 --> 07:14.521
-EXCUSE ME, BUT I OWN THIS
RESTAURANT AND I REALLY DON'T

07:14.651 --> 07:16.740
WANT YOU HITTING UP
ON MY CUSTOMERS, OKAY?

07:16.871 --> 07:19.221
-PERHAPS YOU'D LIKE TO MAKE
A DONATION ON THEIR BEHALF.

07:23.051 --> 07:24.269
HOW ABOUT YOU CAPTAIN?

07:24.792 --> 07:26.010
EVERY LITTLE BIT HELPS.

07:26.924 --> 07:28.448
-TELL YOU WHAT, IF YOU'RE
HUNGRY I'LL BUY YOU LUNCH.

07:29.187 --> 07:30.058
-DIVINE.

07:34.671 --> 07:36.934
COME ON, IT'S OKAY.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.853
MY NAME'S MOLLY, MOLLY KASTEN.

07:43.375 --> 07:44.594
THOUGH I'M THINKING
ABOUT CHANGING IT

07:44.725 --> 07:45.682
WHEN MY ALBUM COMES OUT.

07:45.813 --> 07:46.770
-YOUR ALBUM?

07:46.901 --> 07:48.555
-I'LL BE MAKING IT ANY DAY NOW.

07:48.685 --> 07:50.644
I'M ABOUT TO SIGN A BIG CONTRACT

07:50.774 --> 07:52.341
WITH A MAJOR RECORD COMPANY.

07:52.472 --> 07:54.865
-OH, 'TIL THEN YOU'RE
PANHANDLING ON THE BEACH.

07:54.996 --> 07:58.260
-OH, THIS ISN'T FOR ME,
THIS IS FOR A FRIEND.

07:58.390 --> 08:00.915
THAT'S NOT TO SAY I
COULDN'T USE A SPOT OF CASH

08:01.045 --> 08:03.047
TO TIDE ME OVER TIL
MY SHIP COMES IN.

08:03.787 --> 08:05.528
-HAVE YOU EVER WAITED TABLES?

08:05.659 --> 08:07.922
-SIX YEARS AT MY MUM'S
PUB IN WHITE CHAPEL.

08:08.052 --> 08:10.707
OH, THE CUSTOMERS LOVED ME.

08:10.838 --> 08:12.970
-[CHUCKLING] THERE YOU
GO KAYE, SIGN HER UP.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.016
-YOU'RE LOOKING FOR
SOMEONE TO LEND A HAND?

08:15.146 --> 08:16.670
-DESPERATELY,
WHEN CAN YOU START?

08:16.800 --> 08:19.194
-I'LL KNOCK YOU UP FIRST
THING IN THE MORNING.

08:19.324 --> 08:20.717
-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

08:20.848 --> 08:22.676
-OH, I'LL BE HERE
AT THE CRACK OF DAWN.

08:22.806 --> 08:24.460
-OH.
-YOUR TROUBLES ARE OVER.

08:26.375 --> 08:27.637
-THANK YOU SO MUCH.

08:33.034 --> 08:34.208
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

08:53.707 --> 08:55.273
-HOBIE: HEY DAD, CHECK
IT OUT, IS THAT A BLIMP?

08:55.404 --> 08:57.145
-MITCH: IT'S ACTUALLY
CALLED AN AIRSHIP PAL.

08:57.885 --> 08:58.842
-HOBIE: WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

08:59.582 --> 09:00.975
-MITCH: UM, ASK STEPHANIE.

09:06.154 --> 09:08.460
-HI, YOU MUST BE LIEUTENANT
BUCHANNON, I'M RICHARD BRANSON.

09:08.591 --> 09:09.766
-MITCH: NICE TO MEET YOU.

09:09.897 --> 09:10.637
-RICHARD: AND YOU.
-MY SON, HOBIE.

09:10.767 --> 09:11.725
-HI.

09:11.855 --> 09:13.248
-HI HOBIE, YOU ALL RIGHT.

09:13.378 --> 09:14.510
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.643
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
DOING THIS WATER SKI THING,

09:16.773 --> 09:18.558
IT'S AWESOME.
-WELL, NOT REALLY.

09:18.688 --> 09:20.298
-MITCH: WE'RE GONNA
NEED TO SEE A LAYOUT

09:20.429 --> 09:22.039
OF THE WHOLE OPERATION SO
WE CAN BLOCK THE AREA OFF.

09:22.170 --> 09:24.172
-WELL I HAVE A BLUEPRINT
FOR THE ENTIRE OPERATION,

09:24.302 --> 09:25.086
DO YOU WANNA COME AND LOOK?

09:25.216 --> 09:26.304
-MITCH: ABSOLUTELY.

09:26.435 --> 09:27.697
-RICHARD: COME
AND HAVE A LOOK.

09:27.828 --> 09:29.046
-MAIN ISSUE HERE
REALLY IS JUST SAFETY.

09:29.830 --> 09:31.483
-WELL I COULDN'T
AGREE WITH YOU MORE.

09:31.614 --> 09:34.095
SAFETY'S QUITE IMPORTANT TO
ME, BUT BELIEVE ME, MITCH,

09:34.225 --> 09:35.836
IF WE WEREN'T ABSOLUTELY
CERTAIN WE COULD PULL THIS OFF

09:35.966 --> 09:36.750
WE WOULDN'T BE HERE.

09:36.880 --> 09:38.142
-TERRIFIC.

09:38.273 --> 09:39.883
-WOMAN: CALL
FOR YOU, MR. BRANSON.

09:40.014 --> 09:40.797
-WOULD YOU EXCUSE US?
I'VE JUST GOT A QUICK CALL.

09:40.928 --> 09:41.755
-NO PROBLEM.

09:52.069 --> 09:53.505
-HELLO RICHARD, THERE YOU ARE.
-YES.

09:53.636 --> 09:54.985
-I'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR YOU EVERYWHERE.

09:55.116 --> 09:56.073
-RICHARD: HELLO GLADYS.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.466
HOW ARE YOU?

09:57.597 --> 09:58.162
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN CALIFORNIA?

09:59.294 --> 10:00.469
-[STUTTERING]

10:01.470 --> 10:04.865
WELL I'VE GOT THIS WORLD
RECORD-BREAKING ATTEMPT

10:04.995 --> 10:06.954
THAT WE'RE HAVING A
GO AT TODAY, WHICH--

10:07.084 --> 10:08.303
WHY DON'T YOU COME DOWN?

10:08.433 --> 10:10.174
-LOVE TO, BUT
I'M IN REHEARSAL.

10:10.305 --> 10:12.002
I CALLED BECAUSE I WANT YOU
TO COME TO MY OPENING NIGHT.

10:12.133 --> 10:13.351
-I'D LOVE TO DO THAT.

10:13.961 --> 10:15.092
I LOOK FORWARD TO
SEEING YOU THEN.

10:15.702 --> 10:16.964
BYE.

10:17.094 --> 10:19.096
-DAD, WAIT A MINUTE,
WASN'T THAT...

10:19.749 --> 10:20.620
-MITCH: UH, YEAH.

10:22.230 --> 10:23.623
-IMPRESSIVE MACHINES,
THESE, AREN'T THEY?

10:24.275 --> 10:25.363
-YEAH, VERY COOL.

10:26.408 --> 10:27.888
ABOUT HOW MUCH DO YOU
THINK ONE OF THOSE COSTS?

10:29.019 --> 10:30.020
-DON'T EVEN THINK IT.

10:30.151 --> 10:31.108
-LOOKS LIKE A LITTLE BIT MORE

10:31.239 --> 10:32.109
POCKET MONEY'S GONNA BE NEEDED.

10:32.632 --> 10:34.068
-IT WAS WORTH A TRY.

10:34.198 --> 10:35.199
-WHAT DO YOU SAY WE
ALL JUMP ON THE SCARAB

10:35.330 --> 10:36.592
AND CHECK OUT THE COURSE, HUH?

10:36.723 --> 10:37.593
-LET'S DO THAT.

10:40.770 --> 10:42.642
-ANNETTE RUSSELL, KCOP NEWS.

11:06.274 --> 11:08.319
-[PHONE RINGING]

11:10.495 --> 11:12.497
-YEAH, HELLO, TOWER 14.

11:12.628 --> 11:14.064
-STEPHANIE: HAVE
YOU NOTICED THAT
A SURF'S BEEN BUILDING ALL DAY?

11:14.586 --> 11:16.327
COULD BE A LOT OF RIPS IN
THIS SECTION OF THE BEACH.

11:16.893 --> 11:18.547
-YES STEPHANIE, I KNOW.

11:18.678 --> 11:20.462
NOW DO YOU MIND NOT
LOOKING OVER MY SHOULDER,

11:20.592 --> 11:21.637
IT'S DRIVING ME CRAZY.

11:21.768 --> 11:23.204
-I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP YOU OUT.

11:23.857 --> 11:25.467
YOU KNOW IF YOU'D LISTEN
TO SOME OF THE THINGS

11:25.597 --> 11:26.773
I'M TELLING YOU, YOU MIGHT
ACTUALLY LEARN SOMETHING.

11:26.903 --> 11:27.687
-YEAH, I DOUBT IT.

11:27.817 --> 11:28.600
-WHAT'D YOU SAY?

11:28.731 --> 11:30.124
-NOTHING.

11:30.254 --> 11:31.865
NOW DO YOU HAVE ANY MORE
PEARLS OF WISDOM FOR ME,

11:31.995 --> 11:32.822
OR CAN I GET BACK TO WORK?

11:32.953 --> 11:34.084
-NO, THAT'S IT.

11:34.955 --> 11:35.999
-ALL RIGHT THEN,
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

11:38.175 --> 11:38.959
WAIT A SECOND.

11:39.089 --> 11:40.090
-STEPHANIE: WHAT IS IT?

11:40.612 --> 11:42.223
-I'M GONNA GO MAKE A
PREVEN ON THESE PEOPLE.

11:42.353 --> 11:43.615
-WHAT PEOPLE?

11:43.746 --> 11:44.660
-RIGHT THERE,
RIGHT IN BETWEEN US.

11:44.791 --> 11:46.053
THE GUY AND THE GIRL STEPHANIE.

11:46.183 --> 11:47.228
-YOU MAY NEED
MORE THAN A PREVEN,

11:47.358 --> 11:48.142
THAT GUY'S IN TROUBLE.

11:48.272 --> 11:49.056
BACK ME UP!

11:49.186 --> 11:50.057
-NO, YOU BACK ME UP!

11:51.362 --> 11:54.583
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:14.516 --> 12:16.823
-[GASPING]

12:31.489 --> 12:32.534
-TAKE IT EASY.

12:47.201 --> 12:49.377
CALM DOWN, I'VE GOT YOU.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.033
-STEPHANIE: NEED SOME HELP?

12:54.295 --> 12:55.165
-NO.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.473
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

13:03.957 --> 13:05.567
-OH THAT'S LOVELY.

13:05.697 --> 13:07.047
WHAT FLAVOR IS IT?

13:07.177 --> 13:09.876
-THIS IS MY SPECIALTY,
TUTTI FRUTTI.

13:12.008 --> 13:14.576
GOOD GOLLY MISS MOLLY,
YOU SHOULDN'T DO THAT.

13:15.664 --> 13:17.013
-HOW'S MY BLT DOING?

13:17.753 --> 13:19.624
[BABBLING]

13:22.671 --> 13:24.978
-WAIT A MINUTE,
IT'S NOT READY YET.

13:27.937 --> 13:29.547
[BABBLING]

13:30.679 --> 13:32.028
IT'S READY.

13:44.301 --> 13:45.650
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:48.523 --> 13:50.220
OKAY, GO AHEAD.

13:53.745 --> 13:55.486
THAT'S ALL I CAN SPARE.

13:55.617 --> 13:58.576
YOU CAN'T BE HANGING AROUND
HERE, I'VE GOT WORK TO DO.

13:59.447 --> 14:01.014
LOOK, I'LL COME
BY WHEN I GET OFF.

14:01.144 --> 14:02.537
I'LL BRING YOU
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

14:03.712 --> 14:04.626
I'VE GOTTA GO.

14:15.419 --> 14:16.507
HERE YOU ARE CAPTAIN.

14:17.334 --> 14:18.292
-THANKS MOLLY.

14:18.422 --> 14:19.989
WHOA, HO HO.

14:20.120 --> 14:21.599
THERE'S ONLY HALF A SANDWICH
HERE, WHAT HAPPENED?

14:21.730 --> 14:22.862
-WELL THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.386
HOW THE DEVIL DID THAT HAPPEN?

14:25.995 --> 14:27.344
LET ME GO TALK TO THE COOK.

14:27.475 --> 14:29.085
-OH MOLLY, MOLLY,
WHO WAS THAT GIRL

14:29.216 --> 14:30.434
YOU JUST SHARED
MITCH'S LUNCH WITH?

14:30.565 --> 14:31.522
-WHAT GIRL?

14:31.653 --> 14:33.350
-THE ONE THAT WAS HERE ALL DAY.

14:33.481 --> 14:34.395
I MEAN, WHO IS SHE?

14:38.790 --> 14:40.488
-WE MET A COUPLE OF WEEKS BACK

14:40.618 --> 14:41.837
WHEN I WAS WORKING ON
THE BOARDWALK IN VENICE.

14:42.490 --> 14:44.492
I SUPPOSE I JUST TOOK
HER UNDER MY WING.

14:45.319 --> 14:46.842
WELL SHE'S BEEN LIKE
MY SHADOW SINCE THEN.

14:49.758 --> 14:50.802
-WHAT'S HER STORY?

14:51.455 --> 14:52.761
-ALL I KNOW IS
SHE CAME TO VENICE

14:52.892 --> 14:53.980
BECAUSE OF THE SHELTER HOUSE.

14:54.110 --> 14:55.285
-THE RUNAWAY SHELTER?

14:55.416 --> 14:57.287
-YEAH, AND THAT
CLOSED LAST MONTH.

14:57.418 --> 14:59.072
THEY LOST THEIR FUNDING.

14:59.202 --> 15:00.638
-THAT'S WHY THEY'RE LIVING
ON THE STREETS RIGHT NOW.

15:00.769 --> 15:01.857
A WHOLE PACK OF 'EM.

15:02.510 --> 15:03.990
YOU WOULDN'T KNOW
THEY WERE THERE

15:04.120 --> 15:05.730
UNLESS YOU KNEW THEIR
SECRET HIDING PLACES.

15:06.731 --> 15:08.081
I WAS ABOUT TO TAKE
HER MY TIP MONEY.

15:08.995 --> 15:10.083
-YOU MIND IF I TAG ALONG?

15:10.213 --> 15:11.432
-WHY NOT?

15:11.562 --> 15:13.260
BUT LET ME GET YOUR
SANDWICH FIRST.

15:16.350 --> 15:18.918
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

15:24.314 --> 15:25.098
-HI.

15:25.228 --> 15:26.012
-HEY.

15:26.142 --> 15:27.535
-WHERE'S CAROLINE?

15:27.665 --> 15:28.928
-I SAW HER IN THE LOCKER
ROOM A FEW MINUTES AGO.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.581
SHE WAS LACING UP BOXING GLOVES.

15:31.104 --> 15:32.235
-BOXING GLOVES?

15:32.366 --> 15:33.367
-YEAH, IT SEEMED LIKE SHE HAD

15:33.497 --> 15:34.281
SOME FRUSTRATIONS TO WORK OUT.

15:34.803 --> 15:35.760
SHE AND LOGAN HAVING PROBLEMS?

15:36.544 --> 15:37.893
-NO, NOT THAT I KNOW OF.

15:38.024 --> 15:39.460
-WELL SOMEBODY'S
GOT HER PRETTY UPSET.

15:40.504 --> 15:41.984
-OH YEAH, PROBABLY ME.

15:42.115 --> 15:44.595
-AH, THAT WAS MY NEXT GUESS.

15:45.335 --> 15:46.293
-LOOK, SHE'S JUST
MAD AT ME 'CAUSE

15:46.423 --> 15:47.381
SHE THINKS I'M HOLDING HER BACK.

15:48.034 --> 15:49.557
-WELL ARE YOU?

15:49.687 --> 15:51.689
-NO, ROOKIES ARE SUPPOSED
TO PROVE THEMSELVES.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.127
-STEPHANIE, SHE
HAS PROVEN HERSELF.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.564
MAYBE NOT TO YOU, BUT TO
EVERYBODY ELSE AROUND HERE.

15:57.173 --> 15:58.000
THINK ABOUT IT.

15:59.436 --> 16:00.263
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

16:24.374 --> 16:26.333
-YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE
READY TO STEP IN THE RING.

16:29.945 --> 16:31.251
KEEP YOUR GUARD UP WHEN YOU JAB.

16:32.687 --> 16:34.950
-ARE YOU AWARE THAT YOU'RE
ALWAYS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?

16:37.909 --> 16:40.390
-GUESS AFTER 22 YEARS I
FIGURED YOU'D BE USED TO IT.

16:43.654 --> 16:45.569
-YOU KNOW I'VE WORKED REALLY
HARD AT BECOMING A LIFEGUARD,

16:46.701 --> 16:48.355
AND I'M NOT SAYING I KNOW
ALL THERE IS TO KNOW,

16:48.485 --> 16:49.573
BUT I THINK I'M PRETTY GOOD.

16:49.704 --> 16:51.184
-YOU'RE VERY GOOD, CAROLINE.

16:52.620 --> 16:53.621
I GUESS THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

16:54.404 --> 16:55.405
-WHY IS THAT A PROBLEM?

16:58.365 --> 16:59.540
-I DON'T KNOW, I GUESS I...

17:01.237 --> 17:02.717
STILL WANNA THINK OF
YOU AS MY LITTLE SISTER.

17:04.196 --> 17:07.113
NOT SOME YOUNG HOT SHOT
WHO BEAT ME TO A RESCUE.

17:09.028 --> 17:11.334
-I DON'T THINK OF US AS BEING
IN COMPETITION, STEPHANIE.

17:12.553 --> 17:14.294
-ALL LIFEGUARDS
ARE IN COMPETITION.

17:15.121 --> 17:17.513
I MEAN THE FASTEST
SWIMMER, STRONGEST RUNNER,

17:18.037 --> 17:19.038
JUST COMES WITH THE TERRITORY.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.867
I JUST DON'T WANT IT
TO COME BETWEEN US.

17:23.867 --> 17:26.609
-IT WON'T, I PROMISE.

17:27.133 --> 17:28.308
-HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:31.876 --> 17:33.878
-MAYBE NEXT TIME I'LL
LET YOU MAKE THE RESCUE.

17:35.793 --> 17:38.144
-DON'T PUSH YOUR
LUCK, LITTLE SISTER.

17:42.670 --> 17:44.933
-MAKE SURE WE GOT RESCUE
CANS, LIFE JACKETS,

17:45.064 --> 17:46.500
HERE'S THE FIRST AID KIT.

17:46.630 --> 17:47.892
-AND WHAT ARE YOU GONNA GET?

17:48.023 --> 17:49.590
-UH, COFFEE AND DONUTS.

17:49.720 --> 17:51.331
-MATT: CREAM AND SUGAR PLEASE.

17:54.203 --> 17:55.596
-WELL WHAT DO YOU MEAN
THE WHOLE THING'S OFF?

17:55.726 --> 17:57.728
YOU SAID IT WAS
WRITTEN IN STONE.

18:00.035 --> 18:01.732
CAN'T WE TAKE IT TO
ANOTHER RECORD COMPANY?

18:03.560 --> 18:05.040
YOU SAID I WAS GONNA BE A STAR.

18:07.477 --> 18:10.393
OH SHUT UP, I DON'T WANNA LISTEN
TO ANYMORE OF YOUR RUBBISH.

18:17.008 --> 18:17.879
-THANKS.

18:18.880 --> 18:20.969
YOU KNOW, KAYE, I MADE A
COUPLE OF CALLS LAST NIGHT

18:21.100 --> 18:23.014
AND YOU KNOW IT TURNS OUT
THAT THERE'S A GROUP OF PEOPLE

18:23.145 --> 18:24.320
WHO ARE TRYING TO RAISE MONEY

18:24.451 --> 18:25.887
TO REOPEN THE VENICE
RUNAWAY SHELTER?

18:26.017 --> 18:27.541
-YEAH, AND YOU
TOLD THEM I'D STAGE

18:27.671 --> 18:29.325
A BENEFIT CONCERT
AT THE SANDY CAY.

18:30.413 --> 18:31.806
-HOW'D YOU FIND OUT?

18:31.936 --> 18:33.329
-THEY CALLED ME THIS MORNING.

18:33.460 --> 18:34.983
-WELL THE KIDS DO
NEED A PLACE TO STAY.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.680
-DON'T WORRY, I SAID YES.

18:36.811 --> 18:38.073
AS A MATTER OF FACT,

18:38.204 --> 18:39.727
I'VE LINED UP
SOMEBODY REALLY BIG.

18:41.642 --> 18:43.513
MOLLY, OH MOLLY, WHAT HAPPENED?

18:44.123 --> 18:45.472
-MY RECORD DEAL FELL THROUGH.

18:47.474 --> 18:49.389
SEEMS I WON'T BE CUTTING
MY OWN ALBUM AFTER ALL.

18:49.519 --> 18:51.652
-HEY, YOU'RE GONNA
GET ANOTHER CHANCE.

18:52.348 --> 18:53.915
DON'T GIVE UP ON YOURSELF.

18:54.045 --> 18:55.656
-YEAH, WHO KNOWS,
YOU MIGHT WAIT ON SOME

18:55.786 --> 18:57.875
BIG TIME RECORD PRODUCER
RIGHT HERE AT THE SANDY CAY.

18:58.485 --> 18:59.486
-FAT CHANCE.

19:05.100 --> 19:06.101
WHAT'LL IT BE?

19:09.148 --> 19:11.019
COME ON, I HAVEN'T GOT ALL DAY.

19:12.673 --> 19:13.587
ROBERT.

19:15.589 --> 19:16.590
-ROBERT: MOLLY!

19:17.678 --> 19:18.635
PLEASE WAIT!

19:20.420 --> 19:23.074
-[ROCK MUSIC]

19:35.522 --> 19:37.611
DAMN, WHERE DID SHE GO?

19:38.438 --> 19:41.354
-HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

19:42.050 --> 19:43.269
-I'M LOOKING FOR MY FIANCE.

19:44.095 --> 19:45.314
-YOUR FIANCE?

19:50.058 --> 19:51.364
-WHERE DID I GO WRONG?

19:53.409 --> 19:54.845
WHY WOULD A WOMAN
CHOOSE TO TRAVEL

19:54.976 --> 19:56.934
HALFWAY AROUND THE WORLD
RATHER THAN MARRY ME?

19:57.065 --> 19:58.980
-MOLLY DIDN'T COME HERE
TO GET AWAY FROM YOU,

19:59.110 --> 20:01.069
SHE CAME HERE BECAUSE
LOS ANGELES IS THE CENTER

20:01.200 --> 20:04.072
OF THE MUSIC BUSINESS, AND
SHE WANTS TO BE A SINGER.

20:04.203 --> 20:06.074
-YES, WELL THAT'S
JUST PREPOSTEROUS.

20:06.683 --> 20:08.207
I JUST CAN'T UNDERSTAND
WHY SHE INSISTS

20:08.337 --> 20:11.122
ON PURSUING THIS
CHILDISH DREAM OF HERS.

20:11.253 --> 20:12.994
-WHY DON'T YOU SHARE HER DREAM?

20:14.256 --> 20:15.866
-MOLLY HAS A LOT OF TALENT,

20:15.997 --> 20:17.912
AND YOU SHOULD BE
HER BIGGEST FAN.

20:18.042 --> 20:19.261
-I WANNA BE HER HUSBAND!

20:19.783 --> 20:21.655
-YOU NEED TO GET YOUR
HEAD SCREWED ON STRAIGHT.

20:30.794 --> 20:32.666
-WOMAN ON PHONE: HELLO?
HELLO, WHO'S THERE?

20:34.015 --> 20:34.929
HELLO, WHO'S CALLING?

20:35.059 --> 20:35.843
HELLO?

20:35.973 --> 20:36.974
-EXCUSE ME.

20:43.633 --> 20:44.417
HELLO?

20:44.547 --> 20:45.331
-WOMAN ON PHONE: HELLO.

20:45.461 --> 20:46.984
-WHO'S THIS?

20:47.115 --> 20:48.508
-OVER PHONE: THIS IS
PHYLLIS EVANS, WHO'S THIS?

20:53.513 --> 20:54.688
-HEY, YOU KNOW
WHERE THE GPS IS?

20:54.818 --> 20:56.124
I NEED AN EXACT LOCATION.

20:56.255 --> 20:57.604
-IT'S IN THE HULL, I'LL GET IT.

20:57.734 --> 20:58.866
-ALL RIGHT.

21:02.217 --> 21:03.000
-WHAT THE?

21:03.131 --> 21:04.828
-FANCY MEETING YOU HERE.

21:05.351 --> 21:06.352
-MATT: WHERE'D YOU COME FROM?

21:08.136 --> 21:10.181
-IT'S A BIT CRAMPED DOWN
HERE, GIVE US A HAND.

21:11.879 --> 21:14.098
-MOLLY, I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

21:14.229 --> 21:15.839
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN THERE?

21:15.970 --> 21:17.319
-WELL IT WAS THE ONLY
PLACE I COULD FIND TO HIDE.

21:17.450 --> 21:19.495
HOW DID I KNOW YOU'D BE
SHOVING OFF RIGHT AWAY?

21:19.626 --> 21:20.496
-ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE TURNING AROUND.

21:20.627 --> 21:21.497
WE'RE TAKING HER BACK.

21:22.237 --> 21:23.543
-MITCH, WHAT ABOUT
RICHARD BRANSON?

21:23.673 --> 21:24.718
-HE'LL HAVE TO WAIT.

21:25.893 --> 21:27.416
-DID YOU SAY RICHARD BRANSON?

21:27.547 --> 21:28.548
WHY, HE'S A LIVING LEGEND.

21:28.678 --> 21:30.027
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

21:30.158 --> 21:32.291
-HE'S WATER SKIING
BEHIND HIS AIRSHIP.

21:32.421 --> 21:33.944
WE'RE HERE ON SAFETY STANDBY.

21:34.467 --> 21:36.643
-THAT SOUNDS LIKE OUR
RICHIE, I CAN'T MISS THAT.

21:36.773 --> 21:38.688
-[FAKE LAUGHING] I'M
AFRAID YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO.

21:39.298 --> 21:42.126
-OH PLEASE CAPTAIN, I WON'T
GET IN THE WAY. I SWEAR.

21:42.257 --> 21:44.477
CAN'T YOU FIND IT IN YOUR
HEART TO LET ME STAY?

21:44.607 --> 21:46.696
-OH YOU'RE BREAKING
MY HEART, HERE.

21:46.827 --> 21:48.437
-MITCH, IF WE GO
BACK IT'S GONNA

21:48.568 --> 21:50.178
THROW OFF EVERYBODY'S TIMING.

21:52.354 --> 21:54.791
-AH, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

21:54.922 --> 21:57.751
JUST SIT DOWN, SHUT UP,
AND DON'T EVEN SQUIRM.

21:57.881 --> 21:59.318
-OH YES, SIR!

22:00.754 --> 22:01.581
-I'M GONNA REGRET THIS.

22:10.633 --> 22:12.156
-REPORTER: CAN I ASK YOU
A COUPLE OF QUICK QUESTIONS?

22:12.287 --> 22:13.375
-RICHARD: OF COURSE.

22:13.506 --> 22:14.898
-SO RICHARD, ARE YOU NERVOUS?

22:15.029 --> 22:15.856
HOW DO YOU...

22:17.814 --> 22:19.642
[LAUGHTER] GOOD LUCK!

22:19.773 --> 22:20.687
-THANK YOU.

22:27.215 --> 22:28.825
-RIGHT NOW, RICHARD BRANSON

22:28.956 --> 22:30.784
IS GETTING ONTO THE BOAT
THAT IS GOING TO TAKE HIM

22:30.914 --> 22:33.395
TO HIS AIRSHIP WHERE HE WILL
ATTEMPT TO BE ENTERED INTO

22:33.526 --> 22:36.137
THE GUINNESS BOOK OF WORLD
RECORDS FOR WATER SKIING.

22:39.488 --> 22:42.099
MULTI-MILLIONAIRE RICHARD
BRANSON IS NO VIRGIN

22:42.230 --> 22:44.493
WHEN IT COMES TO
DAREDEVIL STUNTS, HE'S SET

22:44.624 --> 22:46.713
TRANSATLANTIC SPEED
RECORDS IN HIS POWER BOAT

22:46.843 --> 22:49.063
AND HE'S THE FIRST MAN TO
HAVE CROSSED THE ATLANTIC

22:49.193 --> 22:52.371
AND THE PACIFIC OCEAN
IN HIS HOT AIR BALLOON.

22:52.501 --> 22:55.374
BUT THAT'S JUST A SET UP
FOR HIS NEXT DARING DO,

22:55.504 --> 22:57.811
WATER SKIING WHILE ATTACHED
TO HIS OWN AIR SHIP

22:57.941 --> 23:01.162
WHICH WILL BE TRAVELING
ABOUT 70 MILES PER HOUR.

23:02.250 --> 23:04.861
ANNETTE RUSSELL, 13 REAL NEWS.

23:10.040 --> 23:12.260
-[ROCK MUSIC]

23:38.112 --> 23:39.156
-IS THAT BEAUTIFUL
OR WHAT, HUH?

23:39.287 --> 23:40.157
-WOW.

23:56.347 --> 23:59.960
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

24:36.170 --> 24:37.084
-GO RICHARD!

24:37.214 --> 24:38.781
-[CHEERING]

24:45.788 --> 24:47.529
-LOOK AT THAT, HE'S CRAZY.

25:12.032 --> 25:14.034
[LAUGHTER]

25:14.164 --> 25:17.124
-[ROCK MUSIC]

25:19.213 --> 25:20.736
-WOW.
-WOW.

25:42.845 --> 25:45.544
-THAT'S IT MR. BRANSON,
WE BROKE THE RECORD.

25:45.674 --> 25:46.545
-YEAH!

25:46.675 --> 25:47.589
-YEAH!

25:47.720 --> 25:48.895
-HE GOT IT MAN, HE GOT IT.

25:49.025 --> 25:50.026
-STEPHANIE: YEAH!
-CAROLINE: YES!

25:51.071 --> 25:52.463
-HE SET THE RECORD.

25:52.594 --> 25:53.726
HE JUST DID IT.

26:01.168 --> 26:03.387
-[SCREAMING]

26:08.871 --> 26:09.742
-WAIT A MINUTE.

26:10.438 --> 26:12.266
MATT, HE'S NOT COMING UP.

26:12.875 --> 26:13.920
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

26:14.050 --> 26:15.051
-I'M GOING IN.

26:17.314 --> 26:18.272
-WE'RE GONNA GO BACK.

26:19.752 --> 26:22.145
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:04.100 --> 27:04.884
-GIVE ME THE KNIFE!

27:05.014 --> 27:06.015
-I'LL GET IT.

27:06.146 --> 27:07.582
-MOLLY, WH--

27:08.627 --> 27:09.540
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:14.850 --> 27:15.677
-MATT: HAND ME THE KNIFE.

27:20.334 --> 27:23.467
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:41.572 --> 27:43.444
-[GASPING]

27:44.097 --> 27:45.620
-RICHARD: MY FOOT IS CAUGHT.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.666
-IT'S OKAY MR. BRANSON,

27:47.796 --> 27:50.146
WE'LL GET YOU OUT OF
THIS MESS IN A JIFFY.

27:58.198 --> 28:00.243
-[CHEERING]

28:09.949 --> 28:12.647
-CONGRATULATIONS MR. BRANSON,
ONCE AGAIN YOU'RE GOING TO BE

28:12.778 --> 28:15.389
IN THE GUINNESS BOOK
OF RECORDS, WELL DONE.

28:15.519 --> 28:16.695
-YEAH, WELL DONE.

28:17.521 --> 28:19.480
-MITCH: CONGRATULATIONS, MATE.

28:19.610 --> 28:21.047
-THANKS TO YOU LADS, I'LL BE
AROUND TO SAVOR MY
MOMENT OF GLORY.

28:21.177 --> 28:23.005
-NO WORRIES MATE,
ALL IN A DAY'S WORK.

28:23.136 --> 28:25.051
-WELL JUST THE SAME,
IS THERE ANYTHING

28:25.181 --> 28:26.313
MAYBE I COULD DO FOR ANY OF YOU?

28:27.009 --> 28:30.186
-WELL, ACTUALLY, THERE
IS SOMETHING YOU COULD DO

28:30.317 --> 28:31.448
FOR ME THAT IS.

28:32.406 --> 28:35.496
I'M A SINGER AND, WELL I WAS
HOPING YOU'D LISTEN TO MY SONG.

28:36.497 --> 28:38.020
-WELL, SINCE YOU
HELPED SAVE MY LIFE

28:38.151 --> 28:39.152
THAT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO.

28:39.282 --> 28:40.457
-YES!

28:40.588 --> 28:42.721
-[LAUGHING]
-[CHEERING]

28:53.514 --> 28:54.471
-YOU QUIT?

28:55.037 --> 28:56.125
WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU QUIT?

28:56.996 --> 28:58.345
YOU CAN'T QUIT.

28:58.475 --> 29:00.086
-AS MUCH AS I'VE GROWN
ATTACHED TO THIS PLACE,

29:01.043 --> 29:02.305
I'M AFRAID I'VE
HAD A BETTER OFFER.

29:04.220 --> 29:06.657
RICHARD BRANSON'S GOT
ME A RECORD DEAL!

29:06.788 --> 29:09.312
-OH, MOLLY, THAT'S TERRIFIC!

29:09.443 --> 29:11.314
CONGRATULATIONS.

29:11.445 --> 29:12.751
-THANKS, KAYE.

29:12.881 --> 29:13.752
-THAT'S GREAT.

29:20.802 --> 29:23.065
DID YOU HAVE THAT
TALK WITH YOUR FIANCE?

29:23.196 --> 29:26.329
-YEAH, I'LL BE RECORDING IN
LONDON SO WE CAN BE TOGETHER.

29:26.939 --> 29:27.896
WHAT CAN I SAY?

29:28.418 --> 29:30.116
THE POOR BOY'S LOVESTRUCK.

29:31.030 --> 29:33.554
ALL OF A SUDDEN HE WANTS TO
BE INVOLVED IN MY CAREER.

29:34.120 --> 29:36.122
NEXT THING YOU KNOW HE'LL
WANT TO BE MY MANAGER.

29:36.818 --> 29:37.993
-DON'T THEY ALL.

29:44.434 --> 29:45.479
-THERE'S SOMEONE
I'VE GOTTA TALK TO.

29:49.265 --> 29:50.092
HI.

29:51.354 --> 29:52.616
-ARE YOU GOING AWAY?

29:52.747 --> 29:55.794
-YEAH, I'M GOING HOME,
WHERE I BELONG.

29:56.751 --> 29:58.057
YOU SHOULD THINK
ABOUT DOING THE SAME.

29:58.709 --> 30:00.059
-NO, I CAN'T.

30:00.189 --> 30:01.321
MY PARENTS HATE ME.

30:01.843 --> 30:02.844
THEY'LL NEVER TAKE ME BACK.

30:03.497 --> 30:05.499
-YOU'VE GOTTA GIVE
'EM A CHANCE, KIT.

30:06.239 --> 30:08.154
I'LL BET THEY MISS YOU
AS MUCH AS YOU MISS THEM.

30:09.285 --> 30:10.809
YOU CAN'T GO ON LIVING THIS WAY.

30:11.766 --> 30:13.289
YOU NEED SOMEBODY
TO LOOK AFTER YOU.

30:34.441 --> 30:35.877
-WOMAN: COME HERE, HUN.

30:36.008 --> 30:39.881
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

31:00.641 --> 31:01.468
-THAT'S HER FAMILY?

31:01.598 --> 31:02.556
-YEAH.

31:03.296 --> 31:04.471
-WELL HOW DID THEY FIND HER?

31:06.038 --> 31:07.169
-THANK YOUR BOSS FOR THAT.

31:09.215 --> 31:10.303
-WE LOVE YOU.

31:29.626 --> 31:31.106
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
